{"parentUuid":null,"isSidechain":true,"agentId":"af29f71b461c23f95","type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":"/sc:analyze --seq\n\nREAD-ONLY analysis only. Do not modify any files.\n\nCompare this assigned file against three refactoring release specs to identify whether each item is REDUNDANT, CONTRADICTED, OVERLAPPING, or UNAFFECTED.\n\nShared context:\nThe v3.5RigorFlowMerger improve-*.md files were written BEFORE these three refactoring releases were designed. The refactoring releases may render improve-file items:\n- REDUNDANT: the refactor already implements what the improve item proposes\n- CONTRADICTED: the refactor makes the improve item's target file/system incompatible or replaced\n- OVERLAPPING: partial overlap — the refactor implements some of the item but not all\n- UNAFFECTED: no relationship; item stands independently\n\nReference specs:\n1. /config/workspace/IronClaude/.dev/releases/backlog/v3.0_fidelity-refactor_/wiring-verification-gate-v1.0-release-spec.md\n2. /config/workspace/IronClaude/.dev/releases/backlog/v3.05_Anti-instincts_/anti-instincts-gate-unified.md\n3. /config/workspace/IronClaude/.dev/releases/backlog/v3.1_unified-audit-gating-v1.2.1/unified-audit-gating-v1.2.1-release-spec.md\n\nAssigned file:\n/config/workspace/IronClaude/.dev/releases/backlog/v3.5RigorFlowMerger/improve-task-unified-tier.md\n\nFor each item in the assigned file (TU-001, TU-002, TU-003, TU-004), produce:\n\n**ITEM [ID]** — [title]\n- Status: REDUNDANT | CONTRADICTED | OVERLAPPING | UNAFFECTED\n- Evidence: cite specific section/file from which refactor spec(s) create the relationship\n- Recommendation: KEEP-AS-IS | REVISE (describe what changes) | REMOVE (reason)\n\nPay special attention to:\n- TU-001 adds CriticalFailCondition to pipeline/gates.py — v3.1 defines its own normative gate decision contract (Section 5) with blocking check failure rules. Check whether CriticalFailCondition is redundant with v3.1's \"Any blocking check failure => gate failed\" rule (Section 5.2, item 1).\n- TU-001 lists \"Sequential or Serena MCP unavailable\" as a CRITICAL FAIL condition in sc-task-unified-protocol/SKILL.md — v3.1 is about the sprint CLI's audit gate system. Check whether the MCP unavailability condition is still a valid CRITICAL FAIL post-v3.1 or whether v3.1's system_error failure_class subsumes it.\n- TU-002 adds output-type discrimination to sc-task-unified-protocol/SKILL.md tier routing — v3.1 adds sc-audit-gate/SKILL.md and sc-audit-gate-protocol/SKILL.md (Section 10.2, items 3-4). Check for overlap in tier routing logic between the existing sc-task-unified-protocol and the new sc-audit-gate-protocol.\n- TU-004 specifies confidence <0.70 blocking in sc-task-unified-protocol/SKILL.md — v3.1's gate system has its own pass/fail rules (Section 5.2). Check whether TU-004's confidence threshold blocking is aligned with or superseded by v3.1's deterministic gate contract.\n\nEnd with one paragraph summarizing the assigned file's overall disposition after the three refactors."},"uuid":"46c6906c-a22a-4a9a-a75e-9395f59048a9","timestamp":"2026-03-17T18:48:28.214Z","userType":"external","cwd":"/config/workspace/IronClaude","sessionId":"caf57f20-b6f0-47d7-a404-b3840c9c44e5","version":"2.1.77","gitBranch":"v3.0-AuditGates","slug":"bright-juggling-reef"}
