{"parentUuid":"f5f7229e-8943-4117-a70f-9d8e27ed9a96","isSidechain":true,"agentId":"af29f71b461c23f95","message":{"id":"resp_0ddf4b5c326cf9fe0169b9a2555eb48198ade5fdfd5e6988c5","type":"message","role":"assistant","model":"gpt-5.4","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":0,"output_tokens":0},"content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"**Evaluating gate contract transitions**\n\nI'm considering that the gate contract handles completion and release transitions, relying on the latest gate passed rather than classification confidence. So, I wonder if I should categorize it as UNAFFECTED or OVERLAPPING. There's some conceptual overlap in determinism, but they seem functionally distinct. Since the user is asking whether it's aligned with or superseded by, I think UNAFFECTED might be a better choice. I'll weigh that decision.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null},"type":"assistant","uuid":"6ab7acab-f29e-4c25-bfb3-cb7011d7fa02","timestamp":"2026-03-17T18:50:22.278Z","userType":"external","cwd":"/config/workspace/IronClaude","sessionId":"caf57f20-b6f0-47d7-a404-b3840c9c44e5","version":"2.1.77","gitBranch":"v3.0-AuditGates","slug":"bright-juggling-reef"}
