{"parentUuid":"8d71b10c-6acd-409a-94e6-2d2e03bf8803","isSidechain":true,"promptId":"464d4cbe-c91f-4c00-b58c-431d6a3c24cb","agentId":"af29f71b461c23f95","type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"call_FTU0RSLuZWOb5PEq3tpEsfK0","type":"tool_result","content":"{\"thoughtNumber\":4,\"totalThoughts\":4,\"nextThoughtNeeded\":false,\"branches\":[],\"thoughtHistoryLength\":17}"}]},"uuid":"92a8485c-41ab-4f5d-bba4-cfe198187c57","timestamp":"2026-03-17T18:50:41.658Z","sourceToolAssistantUUID":"8d71b10c-6acd-409a-94e6-2d2e03bf8803","userType":"external","cwd":"/config/workspace/IronClaude","sessionId":"caf57f20-b6f0-47d7-a404-b3840c9c44e5","version":"2.1.77","gitBranch":"v3.0-AuditGates","slug":"bright-juggling-reef"}
{"parentUuid":"92a8485c-41ab-4f5d-bba4-cfe198187c57","isSidechain":true,"agentId":"af29f71b461c23f95","message":{"id":"resp_02d384f1501b3ff40169b9a28223f48198a968f3ac3c01da5e","type":"message","role":"assistant","model":"gpt-5.4","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":45580,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":15872,"output_tokens":2148,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"ITEM TU-001 — CRITICAL FAIL Conditions for Unconditional Gate Failure\n- Status: OVERLAPPING\n- Evidence:\n  - The assigned item proposes a new generic `CriticalFailCondition` in `src/superclaude/cli/pipeline/gates.py` and says any matched critical condition should force `gate_passed()` to return failure unconditionally. `/config/workspace/IronClaude/.dev/releases/backlog/v3.5RigorFlowMerger/improve-task-unified-tier.md:25-35`\n  - v3.1 already defines the same core audit-gate outcome as a normative contract: “Any blocking check failure => gate `failed`.” `/config/workspace/IronClaude/.dev/releases/backlog/v3.1_unified-audit-gating-v1.2.1/archive/unified-audit-gating-v1.2.1-release-spec.md:166-172`\n  - v3.1 also standardizes failure handling through failure classes and transition causes, including non-recoverable system failures and `system_error`. `/config/workspace/IronClaude/.dev/releases/backlog/v3.1_unified-audit-gating-v1.2.1/archive/unified-audit-gating-v1.2.1-release-spec.md:155-164`, `/config/workspace/IronClaude/.dev/releases/backlog/v3.1_unified-audit-gating-v1.2.1/archive/unified-audit-gating-v1.2.1-release-spec.md:213-220`\n  - That means the general “unconditional failure on certain conditions” concept is already covered for the new audit-gate system. However, v3.1 does not define TU-001’s exact task-unified conditions, especially “Sequential or Serena MCP unavailable,” “output file absent after max turns,” or “classification header absent.” `/config/workspace/IronClaude/.dev/releases/backlog/v3.5RigorFlowMerger/improve-task-unified-tier.md:28`\n  - v3.0 and v3.05 do not subsume this item; both explicitly fit into the existing `GateCriteria`/`SemanticCheck`/`gate_passed()` pattern without changing core gate infrastructure. `/config/workspace/IronClaude/.dev/releases/backlog/v3.0_fidelity-refactor_/wiring-verification-gate-v1.0-release-spec.md:683-687`, `/config/workspace/IronClaude/.dev/releases/backlog/v3.05_Anti-instincts_/anti-instincts-gate-unified.md:1396-1409`\n- Recommendation: REVISE (remove the broad `CriticalFailCondition` infrastructure change as a generic gate-layer addition, since v3.1 already supplies the normative “blocking check => failed” contract for audit gating. Keep only task-unified-specific failure cases that are still needed, and remap “Sequential or Serena MCP unavailable” to v3.1-style system/transient failure terminology instead of a parallel CRITICAL taxonomy.)\n\nITEM TU-002 — Output-Type-Specific Gate Application\n- Status: OVERLAPPING\n- Evidence:\n  - TU-002 adds output-type discrimination to `sc-task-unified-protocol` and `tier-classification.md`, with categories `code`, `analysis`, `documentation`, and `opinion`, each mapped to different verification behavior. `/config/workspace/IronClaude/.dev/releases/backlog/v3.5RigorFlowMerger/improve-task-unified-tier.md:47-57`\n  - v3.1 introduces a new verification surface centered on audit gating, including `src/superclaude/skills/sc-audit-gate/SKILL.md` for “command behavior/profile/output contract” and `src/superclaude/skills/sc-audit-gate-protocol/SKILL.md` for “deterministic evaluator and transition legality/recovery flow.” `/config/workspace/IronClaude/.dev/releases/backlog/v3.1_unified-audit-gating-v1.2.1/archive/unified-audit-gating-v1.2.1-release-spec.md:336-347`\n  - That creates partial overlap in routing/output-governance responsibility: v3.1 introduces a separate audit-gate protocol layer instead of extending `sc-task-unified-protocol`.\n  - But v3.1 does not define TU-002’s output-type categories or task-unified tier-routing rules, and it does not modify `sc-task-unified-protocol` or `sc-tasklist-protocol/rules/tier-classification.md`. So the specific output-type discriminator remains unimplemented by the refactors.\n  - v3.0 and v3.05 are unrelated to task-unified output-type routing; both target deterministic gates in roadmap/sprint pipelines. `/config/workspace/IronClaude/.dev/releases/backlog/v3.0_fidelity-refactor_/wiring-verification-gate-v1.0-release-spec.md:592-604`, `/config/workspace/IronClaude/.dev/releases/backlog/v3.05_Anti-instincts_/anti-instincts-gate-unified.md:1396-1400`\n- Recommendation: REVISE (keep the output-type discrimination idea, but update it so it does not duplicate or conflict with the new audit-gate command/protocol layer from v3.1. Narrow TU-002 to task-unified pre-routing/classification concerns, and explicitly hand off audit enforcement to `sc-audit-gate`/`sc-audit-gate-protocol` where applicable.)\n\nITEM TU-003 — Six Universal Quality Principles as Verification Agent Vocabulary\n- Status: UNAFFECTED\n- Evidence:\n  - TU-003 is narrowly about adding six named quality principles to `quality-engineer.md` as verification-agent NFR vocabulary. `/config/workspace/IronClaude/.dev/releases/backlog/v3.5RigorFlowMerger/improve-task-unified-tier.md:61-77`\n  - None of the three refactor specs introduce an equivalent change to `quality-engineer.md` or define this six-principle vocabulary as an implementation contract.\n  - v3.1 does mention evaluation notions like completeness/correctness/clarity in review artifacts, but its implementation mapping is about sprint audit-gate models, TUI, audit-gate skills, and tests, not verification-agent NFR vocabulary. `/config/workspace/IronClaude/.dev/releases/backlog/v3.1_unified-audit-gating-v1.2.1/archive/unified-audit-gating-v1.2.1-release-spec.md:336-347`\n  - v3.0 focuses on wiring verification and explicitly preserves the existing gate infrastructure. `/config/workspace/IronClaude/.dev/releases/backlog/v3.0_fidelity-refactor_/wiring-verification-gate-v1.0-release-spec.md:913-914`\n  - v3.05 focuses on anti-instinct deterministic roadmap checks and explicitly reports “Existing model changes: 0.” `/config/workspace/IronClaude/.dev/releases/backlog/v3.05_Anti-instincts_/anti-instincts-gate-unified.md:1404-1409`\n- Recommendation: KEEP-AS-IS\n\nITEM TU-004 — Confidence Threshold <0.70 Explicit Blocking\n- Status: OVERLAPPING\n- Evidence:\n  - TU-004 formalizes that classification confidence below 0.70 blocks execution until user confirmation and requires a structured blocking message. `/config/workspace/IronClaude/.dev/releases/backlog/v3.5RigorFlowMerger/improve-task-unified-tier.md:81-97`\n  - The earlier task-unified comparison material already treated `<70%` as confirmation-blocking behavior, so TU-004 is largely a clarification/refinement of the tier system. `/config/workspace/IronClaude/.dev/releases/backlog/v3.5RigorFlowMerger/comparison-task-unified-tier.md:21-27`, `/config/workspace/IronClaude/.dev/releases/backlog/v3.5RigorFlowMerger/strategy-ic-task-unified.md:31-37`\n  - v3.1 introduces a broader deterministic gate contract requiring failure on unknown/missing deterministic inputs and on any blocking check failure. `/config/workspace/IronClaude/.dev/releases/backlog/v3.1_unified-audit-gating-v1.2.1/archive/unified-audit-gating-v1.2.1-release-spec.md:166-172`\n  - This aligns with TU-004’s “do not proceed on uncertainty without explicit confirmation” philosophy, but it does not directly replace task-classification confidence logic. v3.1 governs audit-gate pass/fail and transition legality, not task-unified classification confidence thresholds.\n  - v3.1 also creates a separate deterministic evaluator surface in `sc-audit-gate-protocol`, which means TU-004 should avoid becoming a second conflicting gate contract. `/config/workspace/IronClaude/.dev/releases/backlog/v3.1_unified-audit-gating-v1.2.1/archive/unified-audit-gating-v1.2.1-release-spec.md:339-340`\n- Recommendation: REVISE (keep the explicit `<0.70` task-classification block, but rewrite it as a task-unified pre-execution ambiguity guard, not as a competing general gate rule. Align the wording with v3.1 deterministic/fail-safe terminology and keep the structured user-confirmation message requirements.)\n\nOverall disposition: `/config/workspace/IronClaude/.dev/releases/backlog/v3.5RigorFlowMerger/improve-task-unified-tier.md` is not wholesale invalidated by the three refactors, but it is no longer cleanly standalone. TU-003 remains intact, while TU-001, TU-002, and TU-004 now partially overlap with v3.1’s newer normative audit-gate contract and skill surface. v3.0 and v3.05 are mostly orthogonal. Net result: the file should be retained only after revision that narrows task-unified items to classification/routing concerns and removes or remaps any duplicated generic gate semantics now owned by `/config/workspace/IronClaude/.dev/releases/backlog/v3.1_unified-audit-gating-v1.2.1/archive/unified-audit-gating-v1.2.1-release-spec.md`."}],"stop_reason":"end_turn"},"type":"assistant","uuid":"42e6a75d-803a-4b5f-8f5b-7eb8820be700","timestamp":"2026-03-17T18:51:27.860Z","userType":"external","cwd":"/config/workspace/IronClaude","sessionId":"caf57f20-b6f0-47d7-a404-b3840c9c44e5","version":"2.1.77","gitBranch":"v3.0-AuditGates","slug":"bright-juggling-reef"}
